                        <td height="63"><img src="../global/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="1"> 
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000" height="8" width="100%" colspan="3"><span class="header">Speed Vs Stall</span></td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#333399" height="2" width="41%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="1%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="58%" bgcolor="#FF9C00"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td></tr></table><TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN=2><SPAN CLASS="header">Rating </SPAN><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/rating/7.gif" BORDER=0></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=23"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=23"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=5632">Kevin "Data's Son" Cline</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Description</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%"><span class=text>This artical will take a look at speed decks
and stall decks and see how they will matchup.</span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Article</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text><br>
Speed decks<br>
Now when we think of a speed deck we generailly think of huge downloads<br>
of personell.reporting cards for free and card drawing mechanisms.Along<br>
with what they can get out and how fast they can get through their missions.<br>
When I think of a speed deck I think of the ferengi.Turn one for them can give<br>
them up to 13 personell on their first turn.And after that a consestant <br>
2-3 personell on each turn afterwards.They are not the greatest though<br>
when it comes to passing dilemmas.As were the federaition can get alot<br>
of personell into play fast and most of them for free and they come with<br>
a ton of skills to easily get past most anything thrown at them.So whats<br>
so great about being able to get everything out fast? Well the faster everything<br>
get&#146;s out into play the quicker you can solve your missions and get to 100<br>
points and win the game.The Dominnion also has the speed factor using Deyos<br>
and the young Jem&#146;hadar and univeral jem&#146;hadar to draw cards and get and extra person<br>
into play at the end of the turn.So speed decks have become quite popular with <br>
passing missions on anywere from the 3rd to 5th turn and winning from anywere<br>
within the 4th-11th turn.But what do we do to stop this? well we can always<br>
keep building better faster decks and just see who can get done with everything<br>
the quickest.Alot of us rely on dilemmas though to slow people down.<br>
<br>
Stall decks<br>
This paragraph will look at stall decks and their usefullness.As mentioned<br>
above speed decks are very popular so of corse people will think of ways<br>
to slow them down but also keep their deck running at a decent pace.So<br>
what&#146;s common for slowing down your oponet? Well their are the Rogue Borg Mercinaries,<br>
Wormholes,Brain drains,Temporal Rift&#146;s,and Barcklays transporter phobia <br>
a personall favorite of mine.Now sience Q-the Referee was introduced into<br>
the game less players have been using the stall taticts because getting <br>
quick access to the card your oponet needs to make them not work just dosent<br>
help your deck any and it means that you have a bunch more of useless cards<br>
in your deck.So what looks like we should all just revert to playing speed decks<br>
right? I dont believe so.Now your oponet still needs to pass missions to<br>
win the game so how do we focus on keeping them away from the missions?<br>
Temporal Rift is always a nice idea it makes their ship vanish for 2 turns<br>
and if they want that AU door to cancel it they must discard their Space-time portal<br>
or grabb it via their tent.Now most players might also have one in their draw deck<br>
just in case but I dont see it to often.And brain drain currently only one card<br>
limites the use of this card to once a turn if I&#146;m correct I might be wrong on that<br>
though cuz I have never used them.They are well setup though for a interesting <br>
way to keep your oponet from his missions. For instance if you use a space/planet <br>
wall dilemma under every one of your oponet&#146;s missions like Shaka when the walls fall<br>
for instance and then use a card thats going to kill off most their crew <br>
and you can brain drain the members with that 1 inportant skill depleating them<br>
from having no more diplomacy will keep them from being able to pass any of their<br>
missions.And now as for the transporter phobia&#146;s they can keep your oponet <br>
from getting to their missions and forcing them into space were well cytherians <br>
and other things can slow them down also a bit. <br>
<br>
Overview <br>
Now I haven&#146;t gone over everything out their I&#146;ve just given a basic look at<br>
some speed decks and some stall decks.The way this game has become though<br>
players keep getting decks to work faster and faster and players keep looking for<br>
ways to slow them down so their deck can have the advantage and win.In the long run <br>
though the deck that can work and win the game the fastest and keep the oponet <br>
from scoring alot of points and winning the game.So any deck that&#146;s going to <br>
fair well aginst a bunch of diffrent decks and oponets is going to be the one<br>
that can outrun and keep their oponet at bay and once your deck can do this <br>
I see it having no trouble winning any local tournament or even worlds.Just<br>
remember though that your oponet will be trying to do the same thing to you.<br>
And good luck on your future games.<br>
<br>
<br>
